OL,3,CCumbrian mum backs campaign for
OL,4,Crestrictions on new drivers
OL,6,F"Passengers in the car may be rowdy,
OL,7,Fthey might not have their seatbelts
OL,8,Fon, they may encourage the driver to
OL,9,Fspeed.
OL,11,F"All of these elements actually add to
OL,12,Fthe risk. We know from countries like
OL,13,FAustralia and New Zealand where they
OL,14,Fhave graduated licences crashes are
OL,15,Freduced from between 20 to 40%."
